description: Portfolio typography - spaced hyphens, no periods on micro headers
alwaysApply: true
---

# Typography: dashes

- Never use the em dash `—` or en dash `–` in user-facing copy, meta descriptions, or alt text.
- Always use a spaced hyphen instead: ` - ` (space, hyphen, space).
- When editing existing content, replace any `—` or `–` with ` - `.
- This applies to HTML case studies, marketing pages, and portfolio copy files.

# Micro headers (section kickers)

- Elements with `class="label"` or `class="mobile-kicker"` must **never** end with a full stop.
- Correct: `CAMPAIGN`, `BRAND PACKAGING`, `POST-REGISTER`. Wrong: `CAMPAIGN.`, `BRAND PACKAGING.`
- When restoring copy from git/Figma/reference files, **always** strip trailing `.` from these tags after merge.
- Do not reintroduce periods from older reference commits.
